metadata.name: Fractal Amoeba #28
metadata.description:
These Amoeba are moving based on mathematics fractal. These mysterious creatures fascinate us. We would lose track of time and keep looking at them.

Controls (in live view):
- Press [e] to update drawing
- Press [0] to increase drawing speed
- Press [9] to decrease drawing speed
- Press [s] to save the screen to a PNG file
- Press [1],[2],[3],[4] to set pixelDensity=1,2,3,4. When you save it, the save image is 1,2,3,4 times resolution.

Create with p5.js
License: CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

metadata.name: CHIP #214
metadata.description:
A CHIP is being constructed by using two brushes that are painting on the board through deterministic noise, and then turned squared and pixelated and blended into each other, with colours selected from 21 different colour schemes. How many iterations, and the speed and size of the added parts determines the final composition. 

You can stop the iterations by pressing S, and download the current composition by hitting D, and restart/reload the iterations by pressing R.

Notes
The thumbnail generation takes a while and the render/iterations in non-GPU browser can be quite slow. Chrome/Firefox recommended.

metadata.name: Appropriate Hidden Breeze #251
metadata.description:
"Appropriate Hidden Breeze" is a study of blending gradients on a grid. 

Dependencies:

Jam3/nice-color-palettes

- Press s: save the current render size
- Press t: scale to screen size
- Press f: full print size 12x12" @ 300 DPI
